|}
But this did not account for the observation of elements heavier than helium. By the end of the conference, Bethe, working in collaboration with [[Charles Critchfield]], had come up with a series of subsequent nuclear reactions that explained how the Sun shines:{{sfn|Schweber|2012|p=347}}
